<p>Yeah, the Foundation wouldn't release humanoids at all.</p>
<p>That was actually an issue with the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-103">Never-Hungry Man</a> (real-world, not in-universe). The original article had him as just never needing sustenance w/o any reason why, so they let him go. That simple, kinda-sorta happy ending was&#8230; unsatisfactory to some people, and the article got editted into its current horrific form.</p>
<p>There's also an example in <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-105">Iris'</a> article of what the Foundation does even IF it appears that anomalous traits have vanished off a humanoid.</p>

