<blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>There's something soothing about having.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Feels like there's a word missing somewhere in there.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>No, gerunds are nouns and can be the direct object of a prepositional phrase, even if you are more used to seeing them as a noun complement. This sentence is saying the act of possession (having) is itself soothing, independent of the possessions.</p>

